# UI Design Patterns

## Color Usage

### Primary Colors
- **Primary**: `hsl(250 100% 60%)` - Main brand color for buttons, links, and active states
- **Primary Hover**: `hsl(250 100% 60%)` - Hover state for primary elements
- **Primary Foreground**: `hsl(210 40% 98%)` (light) / `hsl(0 0% 98%)` (dark) - Text on primary backgrounds

### Secondary Colors
- **Secondary**: `hsl(210 40% 96.1%)` (light) / `hsl(215.3 25% 26.7%)` (dark) - Secondary UI elements
- **Secondary Hover**: `hsl(226.5 100% 93.9%)` (light) / `hsl(215.3 19.3% 34.5%)` (dark) - Hover state for secondary elements
- **Secondary Foreground**: `hsl(222.2 47.4% 11.2%)` (light) / `hsl(0 0% 98%)` (dark) - Text on secondary backgrounds

### Accent Colors
- **Accent**: `hsl(226.5 100% 93.9%)` (light) / `hsl(240 3.7% 15.9%)` (dark) - Accent elements and highlights
- **Accent Hover**: `hsl(229.7 93.5% 81.8%)` - Hover state for accent elements
- **Accent Foreground**: `hsl(222.2 47.4% 11.2%)` (light) / `hsl(0 0% 98%)` (dark) - Text on accent backgrounds

### Semantic Colors
- **Success**: `hsl(142.1 70.6% 45.3%)` - Success states and confirmations
- **Warning**: `hsl(38 92% 50%)` (light) / `hsl(48 96% 89%)` (dark) - Warning states and important notifications
- **Warning Foreground**: `hsl(48 96% 89%)` (light) / `hsl(38 92% 50%)` (dark) - Text on warning backgrounds
- **Destructive**: `hsl(0 84.2% 60.2%)` (light) / `hsl(0 72.2% 50.6%)` (dark) - Error states and destructive actions
- **Destructive Hover**: `hsl(0 84.2% 60.2%)` (light) / `hsl(0 84.2% 60.2%)` (dark) - Hover state for destructive elements
- **Destructive Foreground**: `hsl(210 40% 98%)` (light) / `hsl(0 85.7% 97.3%)` (dark) - Text on destructive backgrounds

### Background Colors
- **Background**: `hsl(0 0% 100%)` (light) / `hsl(221.5 46.4% 11%)` (dark) - Main background
- **Background 400**: `hsl(212.7 26.8% 83.9%)` (light) / `hsl(215 20.2% 65.1%)` (dark) - Light background variant
- **Background 700**: `hsl(210 40% 96.1%)` (light) / `hsl(215.3 25% 26.7%)` (dark) - Medium background variant
- **Background 800**: `hsl(210 40% 96.1%)` (light) / `hsl(217.2 33.3% 17.1%)` (dark) - Dark background variant
- **Background 900**: `hsl(0 0% 100%)` (light) / `hsl(221.5 46.4% 11%)` (dark) - Darkest background variant

### Text Colors
- **Foreground**: `hsl(222.9 84% 4.9%)` (light) / `hsl(0 0% 98%)` (dark) - Primary text color
- **Muted Foreground**: `hsl(215.4 16.3% 46.9%)` (light) / `hsl(240 5% 64.9%)` (dark) - Secondary text color

### Chart Colors
- **Chart 1**: `hsl(221.2 83.2% 53.3%)` - Primary chart color
- **Chart 2**: `hsl(212 95% 68%)` - Secondary chart color
- **Chart 3**: `hsl(216 92% 60%)` - Tertiary chart color
- **Chart 4**: `hsl(210 98% 78%)` - Quaternary chart color
- **Chart 5**: `hsl(212 97% 87%)` - Quinary chart color

### Usage Guidelines
- Use primary colors for main CTAs and important actions
- Use secondary colors for less prominent UI elements
- Use accent colors for highlights and special elements
- Use semantic colors appropriately (success for confirmations, destructive for errors)
- Maintain consistent color usage across light and dark themes
- Ensure proper contrast ratios for accessibility

## UI Components

### Button Patterns

- Primary buttons should be solid with the primary color
- Secondary buttons should have a border with transparent or light background
- Danger buttons should use the error color
- Use consistent padding, border radius, and hover states for all buttons
- Follow fixed button sizes based on their importance and context
- Include appropriate loading states for async actions

### Card Design

- Use consistent border radius (`rounded-lg`) for all cards
- Apply light shadows (`shadow-sm`) for elevation
- Maintain consistent padding inside cards (`p-4` or `p-6`)
- Use subtle borders for card separation
- Ensure proper spacing between card elements

### Form Elements

- Apply consistent styling to all form inputs
- Use clear visual indicators for focus, hover, and error states
- Group related form elements with appropriate spacing
- Provide clear validation feedback
- Ensure proper labeling and accessibility

## Layout Principles

- Use a consistent grid system throughout the application
- Apply proper spacing between elements (8px, 16px, 24px increments)
- Ensure proper alignment of elements (left, center, or right)
- Maintain a clear visual hierarchy with proper sizing and spacing
- Use responsive layouts that work across different device sizes

## Accessibility Best Practices

- Maintain a minimum contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for text
- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- Include appropriate ARIA attributes for complex components
- Provide alternative text for images and icons
- Support screen readers with semantic HTML elements
